e Utopie des »kollektiven Intellektuellen« - und die Versuche ihrer Verwirklichung in Forschung und politischem Engagement.  aThe »Bourdieu phenomenon« in a new light. In his long and close collaboration with Pierre Bourdieu, Franz Schultheis has been able to gain insights into his life and work that open up a largely unknown perspective. In contrast to the usual portraits of Bourdieu as an outstanding social scientist, here the »patron« of a sociological workshop appears on the scene. The description of various aspects of the everyday practice of his Centre de Sociologie Européenne assumes the character of an »ethnography« of working with Bourdieu. Crucial to him, but diametrically opposed to his own fame, is the ideal of the »collective intellectual«, and the attempt to realize it in research and political commitment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aForschungspraxis. 4aFranzösische Soziologie. 4aGesellschaft. 4aKollektiver Intellektueller. 4aPolitische Soziologie. 4aSozialität. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Praxis. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 4aWissenschaftssoziologie. 4aWissenssoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aCollective Intellectual.  aFrench Sociology.  aHistory of Science.  aPolitical Sociology.  aScience.  aSocial Relations.  aSociety.  aSociological Theory.  aSociology of Knowledge.  aSociology of Science.  aSociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.14361/9783839447864zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de G